verbose_text: The most understood cellular roles of ROCK proteins are stabilization of actin filaments via an inhibitory phosphorylation of LIM kinase, and promotion of cellular contraction and cell substratum contacts via increasing myosin motor protein activity through an activating phosphorylation of myosin light chain and an inhibitory phosphorylation of MLC phosphatase [XREF_BIBR].
evidence: actin filaments via an inhibitory phosphorylation of LIM kinase, and promotion of cellular contraction and cell substratum contacts via increasing myosin motor protein
